1
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:51,670
Dear Wataru,

2
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:54,760
I'm sorry for writing this
letter to you out of the blue.

3
00:00:56,390 --> 00:01:00,599
You must be mad at me
for transferring without saying a word.

4
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,600
I know I did something really stupid.

5
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,140
I'm truly sorry.

6
00:01:06,380 --> 00:01:07,900
I wasn't planning on telling you this,

7
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,800
but I still want you to know.

8
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:13,940
So please let me share
a little about myself.

9
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:19,570
The first time I met you, Wataru,
was at Higashimura Park.

10
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,280
Huh?

11
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:35,260
When I was little,

12
00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:38,070
my mom, who always wanted a daughter,

13
00:01:39,510 --> 00:01:42,070
would often dress me up
in girls' clothes on weekends.

14
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,660
Chiharu, do you want to play too?

15
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:53,710
I'm good.

16
00:01:57,360 --> 00:02:00,090
Let's go look for four-leaf clovers then.

17
00:02:05,180 --> 00:02:06,460
I'm gonna catch you!

18
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:09,670
You're running too fast, big brother!

19
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,960
Wait for me!

20
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:17,820
Watch out!

21
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:21,060
I'm sorry.

22
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:23,700
No, it's okay.

23
00:02:25,580 --> 00:02:27,719
Be careful.

24
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,600
I'm sorry.

25
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:34,710
Isn't that person a little weird?

26
00:02:35,020 --> 00:02:36,740
Yeah, I think so too.

27
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:38,800
They don't look like
a girl, more like a boy?

28
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:43,739
Mom.

29
00:02:43,740 --> 00:02:44,620
Hmm?

30
00:02:44,621 --> 00:02:47,120
I want to blow bubbles.

31
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,790
Sure, let's play.

32
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,680
Here you go.

33
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,000
Chiharu.

34
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,850
Chiharu.

35
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:46,890
Where are you?

36
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:49,020
Chiharu.

37
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:04,070
Ouch...

38
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:11,080
I don't want this anymore.

39
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:12,340
I want to go home.

40
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:23,280
Are you okay?

41
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:27,390
Does it hurt?

42
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:31,230
I'm... I'm fine.

43
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,520
Are you alone?

44
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:37,020
Where's your mom?

45
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,830
I was chasing the bubbles,

46
00:04:41,780 --> 00:04:43,400
and then I lost her.

47
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,450
She's probably over by the plaza.

48
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:48,760
I see.

49
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,500
I'll take you there.

50
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:01,640
Mm...

51
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:13,980
Ah.

52
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:19,310
It got away.

53
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,170
Do you want to play?

54
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:27,320
No.

55
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:33,540
Hey.

56
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:37,080
Why are you wearing girls' clothes?

57
00:05:38,860 --> 00:05:39,940
You can tell?

58
00:05:40,790 --> 00:05:41,790
Yeah.

59
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,940
You're a boy, right?

60
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,940
Do you like wearing this?

61
00:05:50,260 --> 00:05:52,720
I don't like it, but...

62
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:58,000
If you don't like it,
you can just say so.

63
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,200
Huh?

64
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,120
I'm sorry.

65
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:14,590
Did I say something to upset you?

66
00:06:14,660 --> 00:06:15,660
No.

67
00:06:17,430 --> 00:06:18,430
It's not that.

68
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:44,110
Here, take this.

69
00:06:45,970 --> 00:06:48,590
Thank you.

70
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:13,850
On the day my pent-up emotions
finally broke through,

71
00:07:16,650 --> 00:07:18,270
that boy didn't say a word.

72
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:21,060
He just quietly took my hand.

73
00:07:22,730 --> 00:07:28,030
Even without his cape, that boy
was still like a hero from a movie.

74
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:45,170
Thank goodness. I'm so glad.

75
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:50,170
Wataru, where did you go?

76
00:07:50,550 --> 00:07:52,780
Seriously, I was so worried!

77
00:07:54,970 --> 00:07:56,430
What if you got kidnapped?

78
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:58,770
I'm sorry.

79
00:08:02,150 --> 00:08:03,660
Where did you get this?

80
00:08:04,690 --> 00:08:06,210
I traded my cape for it.

81
00:08:06,690 --> 00:08:09,280
What? Honestly.

82
00:08:10,610 --> 00:08:12,550
Your sisters are still looking for you.

83
00:08:13,190 --> 00:08:14,190
Alright.

84
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:15,870
Let's go.

85
00:08:20,130 --> 00:08:23,040
Don't scare me like that again.

86
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:31,010
If you don't like it,
you can just say so.

87
00:08:41,770 --> 00:08:42,770
Mom.

88
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:44,130
Um...

89
00:08:44,770 --> 00:08:46,900
I don't like it.

90
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:48,500
Girls' clothes.

91
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,440
Huh...?

92
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:54,780
I've never liked them.

93
00:08:54,820 --> 00:08:58,080
But you looked so happy,
so I was too scared to say anything.

94
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:03,950
I see...

95
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:06,150
I'm sorry.

96
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:11,440
I didn't notice. I'm so sorry.

97
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:14,010
I'm sorry too.

98
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,570
I'm not a girl.

99
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,720
No, no.

100
00:09:20,930 --> 00:09:23,770
That's not what I meant.

101
00:09:24,173 --> 00:09:26,533
I just thought you looked so cute,
and I couldn't help it...

102
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:30,250
You must have been so uncomfortable.

103
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:35,450
I won't do it again.

104
00:09:35,890 --> 00:09:38,590
I'm truly sorry.

105
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:43,710
Mom

106
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:47,060
loves you just the way you are, Chiharu.

107
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:50,270
I'll always love you.

108
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:58,090
When I was too afraid to speak up,
that boy was the one who changed me.

109
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:02,900
"My Summer Of You"
(Episode 5)

110
00:12:07,490 --> 00:12:09,060
Sorry to keep you waiting.

111
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:12,410
Your dad said he needs
to buy a few more things.

112
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:13,929
Souvenirs?

113
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:14,930
Yeah.

114
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:19,400
I heard the people at his company there
asked him to pick some things up.

115
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:21,030
That's rough.

116
00:12:30,090 --> 00:12:32,250
Are you sure about this?

117
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:33,960
Huh?

118
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:38,660
I heard from Teacher Yamada.

119
00:12:39,990 --> 00:12:45,180
You asked him not to tell your
classmates that you're moving to Canada.

120
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:53,350
You didn't even tell the friend
you hung out with over summer break?

121
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,520
Yeah.

122
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:57,940
Why not?

123
00:13:00,690 --> 00:13:04,090
Because I don't think he'd
really care even if I was gone.

124
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:09,890
You feel differently now, don't you?

125
00:13:10,330 --> 00:13:12,140
I think there's still time.

126
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:13,760
It's too late.

127
00:13:19,510 --> 00:13:20,510
I see.

128
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:24,250
That's a shame.

129
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:28,390
I was hoping to meet him too.

130
00:13:28,930 --> 00:13:31,570
Chiharu's high school friend.

131
00:13:39,370 --> 00:13:45,200
I reunited with that boy at our
high school entrance ceremony.

132
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:54,250
Ah, Wataru!

133
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:57,670
Oh, Guchi.

134
00:14:05,430 --> 00:14:07,669
Wataru, where did you go?

135
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:09,890
Seriously, I was so worried!

136
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:18,900
Wataru?

137
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:23,110
Chiharu, let's go.

138
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:24,330
Okay.

139
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:32,840
At the time, I just thought he looked a
lot like that boy from my distant memories.

140
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,920
I've always liked you, Saeki senpai.

141
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:40,930
I'm sorry.

142
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,750
I already have someone I like.

143
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:54,640
Even so, just the thought
that he might be nearby

144
00:14:56,470 --> 00:15:02,830
made me start using "I have someone I like"
as an excuse to turn down confessions.

145
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:15,950
- Hey, hey, sorry.
- Sorry.

146
00:15:16,450 --> 00:15:17,620
Wait.

147
00:15:25,330 --> 00:15:26,050
Here.

148
00:15:26,051 --> 00:15:27,130
Ah, thanks.

149
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:29,130
It flew over there.

150
00:15:29,930 --> 00:15:31,030
Are you okay?

151
00:15:33,110 --> 00:15:34,110
Yeah.

152
00:15:36,050 --> 00:15:37,050
There we go.

153
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:38,750
That was exhausting.

154
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:45,940
Ah, sorry.

155
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:51,070
I'll take you there.

156
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:03,349
Hey, Wataru! If you don't hurry,
the bread will be sold out!

157
00:16:03,350 --> 00:16:04,500
Ah, my bad, my bad!

158
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:06,380
Give me a sec. Here.

159
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:09,260
I have to get some today.

160
00:16:09,310 --> 00:16:10,426
It's definitely gonna sell out fast.

161
00:16:10,450 --> 00:16:11,450
For real.

162
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:13,470
Finally, on that day,

163
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:17,930
I was finally certain that
the boy was you, Wataru.

164
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:24,020
From then on,
my eyes couldn't help but follow you.

165
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:32,530
No, no, no, no, no, no.

166
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,490
So scary, so scary, so scary.

167
00:16:53,090 --> 00:16:55,150
It's okay if you don't remember me.

168
00:16:56,950 --> 00:17:00,270
But I still wanted to talk to you.

169
00:17:16,070 --> 00:17:17,550
Alright, I might as well just buy it.

170
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:20,449
Ah, my bad.
I wasn't watching where I was going.

171
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:21,450
It's fine.

172
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:23,596
I should be the one apologizing.

173
00:17:23,620 --> 00:17:24,620
Here.

174
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:32,010
Uh, we're in the same grade, right?

175
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:33,970
I think so...

176
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:35,630
I'm Saeki from Class A.

177
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:37,720
I'm Toda from Class B.

178
00:17:38,050 --> 00:17:39,469
Do you like movies?

179
00:17:39,470 --> 00:17:41,220
That one's great.
I love it too.

180
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,470
Huh?

181
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:46,349
That keychain... It's Jet from
"The Jet-Black Hawk," right?

182
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:48,269
Wait, you actually know
"The Jet-Black Hawk"?

183
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:49,270
Yeah.

184
00:17:49,570 --> 00:17:53,989
If you have time,
wanna go somewhere else to chat?

185
00:17:53,990 --> 00:17:55,070
Oh, right.

186
00:17:55,210 --> 00:17:56,529
Let me go pay first.

187
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:57,530
Okay.

188
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,540
This is crazy. It's like I'm being hit on.

189
00:18:09,930 --> 00:18:12,380
As we became friends
and spent time together,

190
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:16,430
every time I felt that same
straightforwardness you had back then,

191
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:21,030
you gradually became
someone special to me, Wataru.

192
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:30,110
So it wasn't a coincidence...

193
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:37,490
The reason I chose "Sea
of Light" for our pilgrimage

194
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:43,120
was because the protagonist, who learns at the end
of his journey that he is loved by his parents,

195
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:47,040
reminded me of myself back then.

196
00:18:48,820 --> 00:18:51,660
What you said to me at the station
when we were hiding from the rain...

197
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,720
Don't worry.

198
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,650
If I don't like it,
I'll just say so.

199
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:06,990
And to think you actually remembered
what happened that day.

200
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:09,809
Come to think of it, I was
here too when I was little.

201
00:19:09,810 --> 00:19:12,360
And I met a little girl who was crying.

202
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:14,570
Huh?

203
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,400
I was really so happy.

204
00:19:19,180 --> 00:19:21,030
I'm sorry for causing you so much trouble.

205
00:19:22,820 --> 00:19:25,580
But you still put up with me.
I'm truly happy.

206
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,400
To me, Wataru,

207
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,520
you'll always be in my summer.

208
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,020
Please take care of yourself.

209
00:20:09,620 --> 00:20:12,520
Thank you for giving me the best memories.

210
00:20:22,550 --> 00:20:23,550
Morning.

211
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,680
Morning.

212
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:35,269
Oh, a love letter?

213
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:36,270
Hey!

214
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,000
(Saeki Chiharu)

215
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,640
Sorry.

216
00:20:50,380 --> 00:20:51,500
He sent you a letter?

217
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,120
Yeah.

218
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,500
I'm sorry.

219
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:01,590
Huh?

220
00:21:01,591 --> 00:21:02,790
- Hey.
- Wait.

221
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:05,070
Is that guy still in Japan?

222
00:21:05,470 --> 00:21:06,120
Huh?

223
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:07,140
Look at the postmark.

224
00:21:07,477 --> 00:21:10,776
It says September 3rd, Tamaki-cho.

225
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,100
Huh? You're right.

226
00:21:17,770 --> 00:21:18,770
Let's go.

227
00:21:24,820 --> 00:21:25,820
Kawaguchi.

228
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:27,596
Do you know where Saeki's house is?

229
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:29,519
Yeah, I know. Why?

230
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:31,080
He might still be there.

231
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:32,539
Can you give me the address?

232
00:21:32,540 --> 00:21:35,299
Uh, it's near the Third Elementary School.

233
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:36,919
Is that in Tamaki-cho?

234
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:37,920
Yeah.

235
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:40,800
Sorry, Guchi.

236
00:21:40,820 --> 00:21:42,920
Once you get the address,
text it to me immediately.

237
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:45,480
And tell our homeroom
teacher I'm leaving early.

238
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:46,919
- I'm off.
- Huh?

239
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:47,920
- What?
- Huh?

240
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:51,350
I can't believe he's leaving early
before the first period even starts.

241
00:21:53,913 --> 00:21:57,303
Kawaguchi, sorry.
Can you tell me Saeki's address?

242
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:58,510
Got it.

243
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,360
Coming.

244
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:22,110
I'm sorry for the sudden intrusion.

245
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,920
I'm Toda.

246
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:26,190
Is Saeki-kun here?

247
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:30,100
Please wait a moment.

248
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:31,960
Okay.

249
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,879
Are you Chiharu's friend?

250
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,100
Yes.

251
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:48,800
Um, I heard he's going to Canada.

252
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:49,870
Ah.

253
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,180
He kept it a secret, didn't he?

254
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:53,450
I'm so sorry.

255
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,260
So, is Saeki...?

256
00:22:57,540 --> 00:22:59,700
There's something I really
need to tell him in person.

257
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:01,920
He's not answering his phone.

258
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:03,980
I'm really sorry.

259
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,170
He's not home right now.

260
00:23:05,460 --> 00:23:07,159
Huh? Did he already leave for Canada?

261
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,160
No.

262
00:23:08,540 --> 00:23:11,240
Only my husband went to Canada first.

263
00:23:11,340 --> 00:23:15,560
Because of school arrangements,
Chiharu won't fly out until tomorrow.

264
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,720
Then where is Saeki now?

265
00:23:20,340 --> 00:23:22,940
He didn't tell me where he was going,

266
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,440
but he said he'd be back before dinner.

267
00:23:31,260 --> 00:23:32,459
Thank you.

268
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:33,460
Huh?

269
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:34,840
Toda-kun.

270
00:23:35,410 --> 00:23:36,660
Don't you have class?

271
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:41,270
I don't know where he could be,

272
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:42,640
but...

273
00:23:45,180 --> 00:23:49,230
I absolutely refuse to
let summer end like this.

274
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,396
(Next Episode Preview)
I want to go to Moriya Beach.

275
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:50,016
I thought I had to stay far away from you.
So far that I'd never see you again.

276
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:52,460
Making decisions alone,
putting an end to things alone.

277
00:24:52,580 --> 00:24:53,780
I want to hear your voice.

278
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,180
I want to see you.

279
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:56,340
I want to touch you.

280
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:58,190
Don't ever show your face to me again.

